      >The Big Short takes a bold and unconventional approach to explaining the 2008 financial crisis, making it both educational and gripping. Through the perspectives of a handful of eccentric investors, the film unveils how the housing bubble and subprime mortgage collapse brought the financial world to its knees.
      </p>
